{% extends 'pub/base.html.twig' %}

{% block body %}
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <section class="bg-slate-900 text-white py-20 relative overflow-hidden border-b-8 border-secondary">
        {% if event_config and event_config.heroImage and event_config.heroImage.imageName %}
            <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-30 bg-cover bg-center" style="background-image: url('{{ ('uploads/' ~ event_config.heroImage.imageName)|imagine_filter('banner_hero') }}'); background-color: #004040;"></div>
        {% else %}
            <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-30 bg-cover bg-center" style="background-image: url('{{ asset('images/hero-bg.jpg') }}'); background-color: #004040;"></div>
        {% endif %}
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6 text-center relative z-10">
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-secondary text-5xl mb-4">groups</span>
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">About the Event</h1>
            <p class="text-secondary text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">Discover the joint assembly of the VIII IRCHLB and XXIV IOCV, their missions, and global history.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- About the Event -->
    <section class="py-24 bg-white">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl" data-aos="fade-up">
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-secondary text-5xl mb-4">info</span>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">About the Event</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-slate-700 mx-auto leading-relaxed space-y-6">
                <p>Brazil, the world's largest producer of oranges and the leading exporter of orange juice, will host the <strong>VIII International Research Conference on Huanglongbing (IRCHLB)</strong> and the <strong>XXIV Conference of the International Organization of Citrus Virologists (IOCV)</strong> from <strong>October 25 to 29, 2027</strong>, in <strong>Ribeirão Preto, São Paulo, Brazil</strong>.</p>
                <p>Recognized as the leading global forums in their respective fields, these conferences will bring together researchers, scientists, citrus growers, representatives of the citrus industry, and plant health authorities from around the world to exchange knowledge and discuss solutions to the most pressing challenges affecting citrus health worldwide.</p>
                <p>Held jointly, the conferences will provide a unique opportunity to showcase the latest scientific advances and strengthen international collaboration in addressing the major phytosanitary challenges affecting citrus production worldwide, particularly <strong>Huanglongbing (HLB)</strong>, the most destructive citrus disease.</p>
                <p>With nearly half of the commercial sweet orange trees in the <strong>Brazilian Citrus Belt</strong>—covering the state of São Paulo and the Triângulo Mineiro and Southwestern regions of Minas Gerais—affected by HLB in 2025, disease incidence continues to increase, although at a slower pace than in recent years, posing significant challenges for both citrus growers and the citrus industry.</p>
                <p>By bringing together experts from different disciplines and countries, the conference will provide an exceptional platform for networking across the citrus value chain, fostering the exchange of knowledge, the development of new collaborations, and the advancement of research to support a more sustainable and resilient citrus industry in the face of HLB and other citrus diseases.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Mission & Objectives -->
    <section class="py-24 bg-white border-t border-slate-100">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl" data-aos="fade-up">
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-secondary text-5xl mb-4">flag</span>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">Mission & Objectives</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-slate-700 mx-auto text-center font-medium leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
                <p>The conference reinforces the international commitment to scientific research, innovation, and the development of collaborative solutions for the future of global citrus production.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- History & Past Editions -->
    <section class="py-24 bg-slate-50 border-t border-b border-slate-200 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-5xl">
            <div class="text-center mb-16" data-aos="fade-up">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-secondary text-5xl mb-4">history</span>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">History & Previous Editions</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
                    The <strong>International Organization of Citrus Virologists (IOCV)</strong> has a long-standing tradition of promoting research and scientific collaboration on <strong>graft-transmissible citrus diseases</strong>, while the <strong>International Research Conference on Huanglongbing (IRCHLB)</strong> is recognized as the world's leading conference dedicated exclusively to Huanglongbing (HLB), the most devastating disease affecting citrus production worldwide.
                </p>
            </div>

